Class AnagramManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • AnagramManager

  • public class AnagramManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This class manages the anagram data structure for a dictionary of words, as well as serving requests for anagrams.
    Since:
    1.0

      • AnagramManager

        public AnagramManager(java.util.List<java.lang.String> listOfWords)
        Constructor, takes an unmodifiable list of words and instantiates a Word object for each, stored in an array. Initializes a map of canonical words to sets of their matching anagrams. Initializes a random object.
        Parameters:
        listOfWords - A List of strings passed to AnagramManager
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if list is null or list length < 1
        Precondition:
        List must not be empty, List must not be null
        Postcondition:
        Instantiates an AnagramManager object with initialized Word array and anagram map
